  "text": "In the present study, seeds of A. lancea obtained in a previous study were used [CITATION_1] . The seeds were originally obtained from the People's Republic of China and were from different genotypes. In other words, the seeds were harvested in natural mating. The plants were identified by the first author himself as A. lancea due to morphological characteristics. A clonal line of A. lancea was propagated from a rhizome of a single plant. Twenty-five clonal lines (line1-line25) with different genotypes were used in the present study. ",
